              <h3 class="title is-4">Shrimp Pad Thai</h3>
              <p>Description: A classic Thai dish featuring succulent shrimp, stir-fried with rice noodles, crunchy peanuts, and fresh herbs in a tangy tamarind sauce. A harmonious blend of sweet, sour, and savory flavors.</p>
               <div class="recipe-details" style="max-height: 300px; overflow-y: auto;">
          <h4 class="subtitle is-5">Ingredients</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>8 oz rice noodles</li>
        <li>1/2 lb large shrimp, peeled and deveined</li>
        <li>2 eggs, lightly beaten</li>
        <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
        <li>1 cup bean sprouts</li>
        <li>1/2 cup green onions, chopped</li>
        <li>1/4 cup roasted peanuts, chopped</li>
        <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
        <li>1 lime, cut into wedges</li>
        <li>Fresh cilantro, for garnish</li>
        <li>3 tablespoons fish sauce</li>
        <li>2 tablespoons tamarind paste</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon soy sauce</li>
        <li>2 tablespoons brown sugar</li>
        <li>1/2 teaspoon chili flakes (adjust to taste)</li>
          </ul>

          <h4 class="subtitle is-5">Preparation</h4>
          <ol>
            <li>Cook the rice noodles according to the package instructions. Drain and set aside.</li>
        <li>In a small bowl, whisk together fish sauce, tamarind paste, soy sauce, brown sugar, and chili flakes to make the Pad Thai sauce. Set aside.</li>
        <li>Heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Add the shrimp and cook until pink and opaque, about 2-3 minutes per side. Remove from the pan and set aside.</li>
        <li>Add the remaining tablespoon of oil to the pan. Add minced garlic and cook for about 30 seconds until fragrant.</li>
        <li>Push the garlic to one side of the pan and pour the beaten eggs into the other side. Scramble the eggs until cooked through.</li>
        <li>Add the cooked noodles to the pan and pour the prepared Pad Thai sauce over them. Toss to combine and coat the noodles with the sauce.</li>
        <li>Add the cooked shrimp, bean sprouts, and green onions to the pan. Toss everything together until heated through.</li>
        <li>Divide the Pad Thai among plates. Top with chopped peanuts, fresh cilantro, and serve with lime wedges.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        
