              <h3 class="title is-4">Beef Souvlaki</h3>
              <p>Description: A Greek favorite, Beef Souvlaki consists of marinated and skewered beef, grilled to juicy perfection. Served with pita bread, tzatziki sauce, and a medley of fresh veggies.</p>
              <div class="recipe-details" style="max-height: 300px; overflow-y: auto;">
      <h4 class="subtitle is-5">Ingredients</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>3 lbs oxtail pieces</li>
        <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
        <li>1 large onion, chopped</li>
        <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
        <li>2 carrots, peeled and chopped</li>
        <li>2 celery stalks, chopped</li>
        <li>2 large potatoes, peeled and cubed</li>
        <li>1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes</li>
        <li>4 cups beef broth</li>
        <li>1 cup red wine (optional)</li>
        <li>2 bay leaves</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon dried thyme</li>
        <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
      </ul>

      <h4 class="subtitle is-5">Preparation</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>Season the oxtail pieces with salt and pepper.</li>
        <li>Heat vegetable oil in a large pot or Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add oxtail pieces and sear until browned on all sides. Remove from pot and set aside.</li>
        <li>In the same pot, add chopped onions, garlic, carrots, and celery. Sauté for about 5 minutes until softened.</li>
        <li>Return the seared oxtail to the pot. Add potatoes, diced tomatoes (with juice), beef broth, red wine (if using), bay leaves, and dried thyme.</li>
        <li>Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low. Cover and let it simmer for about 3-4 hours, or until the oxtail is tender and the meat is falling off the bones.</li>
        <li>Skim off any excess fat from the surface of the stew.</li>
        <li>Discard the bay leaves. Taste and adjust seasoning with salt and pepper, if needed.</li>
        <li>Serve hot and enjoy your delicious oxtail stew!</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
